As the designated administrator, i need to be able to give an access to other
people of my organisation the needed rights and no more,with no possible
confusion, so i need an interface that does not obfuscate what i am doing
and still allows for quick action.

As a data analyst, i need to be able to formulating my ideas fast, so i need
graphs with relevant data out of the box. I also need to be able to examine
data in detail, so i need to be able to consult and export the raw data to
analyse it in another tool.

As a member of human resources, i need to be able to manage teams of people,
wether incoming or outgoing, with a system intuitive enough that i do not
need a full blown formation on how to use the tools and it’s principles.

As a safety officer, I need to monitor the density of people within specific
zones in real-time, so I can ensure safety regulations are followed and react
promptly to overcrowded areas.

As a city planner, I need to track and visualize traffic and pedestrian flow
patterns over time, so I can identify bottlenecks and propose infrastructure
improvements.

As a retail manager, I need access to foot traffic data around my store’s
perimeter and areas leading to it, so I can optimize store placement, staff
allocation, and marketing campaigns.

As a facilities manager, I need real-time alerts about unusually high or low
movement in monitored areas, so I can quickly dispatch resources to investigate
and address any irregularities.

As an event organizer, I need to see live data on how attendees are moving
between event zones, so I can dynamically manage crowd flow and adjust
entrances or pathways to ensure a smooth event experience.

As an operations manager, I need to measure and compare footfall between key
areas of my business premises over weeks or months, so I can evaluate which
areas contribute most to efficiency and revenue generation.

As a security officer, I need to identify non-typical movement patterns
overnight or in restricted areas, so I can address potential risks such as
trespassing or theft.

As a logistics coordinator, I need an analysis of movement within our
distribution hubs to find unnecessary stagnation points, so I can optimize
the flow of goods and workers to save time and reduce costs.

As a marketing analyst, I need to view heatmaps of high-traffic zones during
specific times or events, so I can better target ad placements and promotional
activities for maximum visibility.

As an auditor, I need access to an immutable log of movement records, segmented
by time and location, so I can investigate security breaches and reconstruct
incident timelines.

As a transportation authority, I need aggregate data on movement trends through
public transport stations, so I can optimize transit schedules and reduce wait
times during peak operations.

As a sustainability consultant, I need to correlate movement data with
environmental factors such as energy usage or emissions, so I can make
recommendations toward more sustainable practices within the territory.

As a business intelligence analyst, I need tools to predict future movement
patterns based on historical data, so I can propose strategic changes to
improve the organisation’s long-term efficiency.

As an NGO worker or community manager, I need to study patterns of movement in
under-served zones, so I can understand community needs and advocate for better
resource allocation.